<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Love Island twins Jess and Eve Gale were pictured looking very glamorous when they left London hotspot Bagatelle on Sunday night. </p>

<p>Jess risked a serious wardrobe malfunction wearing a lace sheer corset which had panels strategically placed to protect her modesty. </p>

<p>She tucked her top into a pair of short denim hotpants, with her sister Eve, both aged 21, wearing a similar pair of shorts. </p>

<p>Racy: Love Island's Jess Gale risked a wardrobe malfunction in a sheer corset as she joined twin sister Eve in matching denim shorts on a night out at Bagatelle in London on Sunday</p>

<p>Daisy Dukes: The twins wore matching denim shorts and matching perspex heels as they posed together for a snap </p>

<p>Eve wore a different top though, opting for a bright yellow satin vest top which showed off her ample assets. </p>

<p>Both ladies, who appeared on the last series of Love Island wore matching perspex shoes, and Jess wore a white satin top worn over her outfit. </p>

<p>Earlier on in the evening, the twins posted content from inside Bagatelle to their Instagram stories. </p>

<p>Sheer delight: Jess teamed her lingerie top with shorts and a satin white top which was slung over her shoulder </p>

<p>They showed off a giant ice-cream dessert which they shared with one another and showed off their fashion looks in greater detail in mirror selfies. </p>

<p>Jess has been trying to move on since her split from Love Island beau Ched Uzor, 23, during the pandemic.  </p>

<p>It's been reported that lockdown made it impossible for the couple to 'build a relationship' as they were unable to meet up with one another. </p>

<p>Bright thing: Eve opted for a bright yellow satin vest top which showed off her ample assets</p>

<p>In a statement shared with MailOnline, the blonde beauty confirmed the COVID-19 lockdown played a role in the demise of their romance, but insisted they continue to be friends. </p>

<p>The statement read: 'After a whirlwind romance in the Love Island villa, unfortunately Jessica Gale and Ched Uzor have made the mutual decision to split.</p>

<p>'They have unfortunately felt the effects of lockdown separation but will continue as friends. </p>

<p>'They wish nothing but the best for each other and full success in each others careers.' </p>

<p>Grub's up! They showed off a giant ice-cream dessert which they shared with one another and showed off their fashion looks in greater detail in mirror selfies</p>

<p>Snap happy: The girls took lots of selfies from inside the venue </p>

<p>Style statement: Eve carried a mini Fendi bag in her hand as she headed home after her night out </p>

